<section id="fb1">
	<p align="left">1. Parents could make sure their children were intelligent.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb2">
	<p align="left">2. Criminals could be 'cured' of their criminal tendencies.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb3">
	<p align="left">3. Could upset natural balances such as the male to female ratio.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb4">
	<p align="left">4. Fatal diseases could be cured.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb5">
	<p align="left">5. Could be controlled by political regimes.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb6">
	<p align="left">6. Children and future generations will not be able to give their consent to genetic changes.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb7">
	<p align="left">7. Parents could choose their children's physical appearance.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb8">
	<p align="left">8. The advantages of gene therapy may only be available to the rich.</p>
</section>
